<h3 id="virtual-assistant-entry-point-ui-design-for-mobile">Virtual Assistant Entry Point UI Design for Mobile</h3>

<p>The screenshots below are taken from the production iOS application.</p>

<p>A key win for the user experience in this project was <em>not</em> placing an entry point for Sandi, our Virtual Assistant, on the login screen, which was already filled with a call-to-action and several secondary buttons.</p>

<p>With the support of the Head of UX and using supporting secondary market research and my analysis of user utterances in Sandi (inputted user text), I worked with developers, the product owner, and the product manager, to not add an unneeded entry point.</p>

<p>Sometimes the biggest UX outcomes are about what <em>doesn’t</em> show up in the UI.</p>

